Author: Tara Nath Subedi <Tara.Subedi@windriver.com>
Date:   Wed May 27 16:15:42 2026 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] phc2sys: skip system clock sync when UTC offset is not valid and traceable -- fix for -O

phc2sys: allow clock sync when -O is used (bypass utc_offset_traceable check)
phc2sys: latch utc_offset_traceable to prevent drift during port state flaps

When the PHC driver initializes, it sets the PHC to the system clock
(UTC). At this point, ptp4l has not yet disciplined the PHC to TAI,
so phc2sys must not apply the 37s UTC-TAI correction in update_clock()
until the PHC is confirmed to be on TAI timescale.

The utc_offset_traceable flag from TIME_PROPERTIES_DATA_SET serves as
this confirmation: when traceable is set, ptp4l has locked to the GM
and the PHC is on TAI. However, in environments where ptp4l port state
flaps between MASTER and SLAVE, the traceable flag also flaps. This
causes phc2sys to repeatedly block update_clock() during transitions,
leaving the system clock undisciplined and accumulating drift.

Once the PHC has been stepped to TAI, it does not revert to UTC on a
port state flap — ptp4l does not step the PHC back when transitioning
to MASTER. Therefore, the traceable check is only needed as a cold
start guard to prevent applying the 37s correction while the PHC is
still on UTC.

Introduce a phc_synced_to_tai latch on the master clock:
- On cold start (phc_synced_to_tai=0): block update_clock() until
	utc_offset_traceable is first seen as true
- Once traceable is observed: set phc_synced_to_tai=1, confirming
	the PHC is on TAI
- On subsequent traceability flaps: the latch remains set, allowing
	update_clock() to continue without blocking

Additionally, when phc2sys is invoked with -O (forced UTC offset),
the PMC agent never queries pmc_agent_query_utc_offset() from ptp4l,
so the utc_offset_traceable flag is never populated and remains false.
Since the user has explicitly provided the offset, the traceable
protection is unnecessary. Gate the entire traceable check on
!priv->forced_sync_offset to bypass it when -O is used.

Behavior summary:
- Cold start, no -O: blocks until PHC confirmed on TAI (first
	traceable=1), then never blocks again
- Port state flap after lock: no blocking, no drift
- -O <offset>: never blocks (user-provided offset, no ptp4l query)

Changes in phc2sys.c:
- Add phc_synced_to_tai field to struct clock
- do_loop: replace unconditional traceable gate with one-shot latch
	on priv->master->phc_synced_to_tai.
	skip traceable check when forced_sync_offset is set
- do_pps_loop: apply same latch logic for PPS path

TEST PLAN:
PASS: A) Setup PTP4L with currentUtcOffsetValid=0, timeTraceable=0
		/usr/sbin/phc2sys -f /etc/linuxptp/ptpinstance/phc2sys-phcinst0.conf
		-s enp81s0f2 -z /var/run/ptp4l-ptpinstc01 -w -m -l 7
		debug message: phcinst0 skipping system clock sync: UTC offset is not valid or traceable
PASS: B) Setup PTP4L with currentUtcOffsetValid=1, timeTraceable=1
		no more shows debug message
		Phc2sys starts syncing system-clock.
PASS: With "phc2sys -a", same result as above A) and B)
PASS: With "phc2sys -O 37", works as below for both A) and B)
		no above debug message
		Phc2sys starts syncing system-clock.
PASS: With "phc2sys -w -O 37", works as below for both A) and B)
		no above debug message
		Phc2sys starts syncing system-clock.
PASS: C) Port state flapping (MASTER<->SLAVE) with traceable flapping
		After initial lock, phc2sys continues syncing through flaps
		without blocking or drift accumulation.

Signed-off-by: Tara Nath Subedi <tara.subedi@windriver.com>
---
 phc2sys.c | 45 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----------
 1 file changed, 34 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

diff --git a/phc2sys.c b/phc2sys.c
index 9494655..077bd5e 100644
--- a/phc2sys.c
+++ b/phc2sys.c
@@ -87,6 +87,7 @@ struct clock {
 	int state;
 	int new_state;
 	int sync_offset;
+	int phc_synced_to_tai;
 	int leap_set;
 	int utc_offset_set;
 	struct servo *servo;
@@ -1034,11 +1035,21 @@ static int do_pps_loop(struct phc2sys_private *priv, struct clock *clock,
 
 		if (pmc_agent_update(node) < 0)
 			continue;
-		/* don't sync system clock when UTC offset is not valid and traceable */
-		if (!pmc_agent_utc_offset_traceable(node)) {
-			pr_debug("skipping system clock sync: "
-				 "UTC offset is not valid or traceable");
-			continue;
+		/* When -O is used, the user has explicitly provided the UTC
+		 * offset and pmc agent does not query utc offset from ptp4l,
+		 * so skip the traceable check. Otherwise, don't sync system
+		 * clock when UTC offset is not valid and traceable.
+		 *
+		 * Once traceable has been seen, the PHC is on TAI and
+		 * will not revert to UTC on a port state flap. */
+		if (!priv->forced_sync_offset) {
+			if (pmc_agent_utc_offset_traceable(node)) {
+				priv->master->phc_synced_to_tai = 1;
+			} else if (!priv->master->phc_synced_to_tai) {
+				pr_debug("skipping system clock sync: "
+					 "UTC offset is not valid or traceable");
+				continue;
+			}
 		}
 		update_clock(priv, clock, pps_offset, pps_ts, -1);
 	}
@@ -1712,13 +1723,25 @@ static int do_loop(struct phc2sys_private *priv, struct config *cfg, int subscri
 			    !strcmp(clock->device, priv->master->device))
 				continue;
 
-			/* don't sync system clock when UTC offset is not valid and traceable */
+			/* When -O is used, the user has explicitly provided the UTC
+			 * offset and pmc agent does not query utc offset from ptp4l,
+			 * so skip the traceable check. Otherwise, don't sync system
+			 * clock when UTC offset is not valid and traceable.
+			 *
+			 * Once traceable has been seen, the PHC is on TAI and
+			 * will not revert to UTC on a port state flap. Latch
+			 * this so subsequent traceability flaps do not block
+			 * clock synchronization causing unnecessary drift. */
 			if (clock->clkid == CLOCK_REALTIME &&
-			    priv->master->node &&
-			    !pmc_agent_utc_offset_traceable(priv->master->node)) {
-				pr_debug("skipping system clock sync: "
-					 "UTC offset is not valid or traceable");
-				continue;
+			    !priv->forced_sync_offset &&
+			    priv->master->node) {
+				if (pmc_agent_utc_offset_traceable(priv->master->node)) {
+					priv->master->phc_synced_to_tai = 1;
+				} else if (!priv->master->phc_synced_to_tai) {
+					pr_debug("skipping system clock sync: "
+						 "UTC offset is not valid or traceable");
+					continue;
+				}
 			}
 
 			if (!clock->servo) {
